3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry): Algebraic geometry is a branch of mathematics that studies geometric objects defined by polynomial equations, which can be applied to computational geometry problems. 
4. cs.SD (Sound): This sub-category includes topics related to signal processing and coding theory, which are relevant to the study of algebraic geometry codes. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may touch upon the computational complexity of encoding and decoding algebraic geometry codes, which can be of interest to researchers in this sub-category.
